    "what_description": "Megastachya tenax is a perennial grass species in the family Poaceae. The plant grows up to 1.5 meters tall with leafy stems and flat, narrow leaves that are typically 10-30 centimeters long and 1-5 millimeters wide. Its inflorescence is a panicle that is 10-40 centimeters long, composed of numerous spikelets, each containing 1-5 florets. The spikelets are 1-5 centimeters long, with a linear or lance-shaped lemma that is usually 1-3 centimeters long. Its native habitats include tropical and subtropical regions of Australia, Africa, and Asia.",
