    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Megastachya tenax are triterpenoids, flavonoids, saponins, phenolic acids, and alkaloids. These compounds have been identified through various studies as the primary bioactive components responsible for the medicinal properties of Megastachya tenax. Specifically, triterpenoids have been shown to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, flavonoids exhibit antioxidant and antimicrobial activities, saponins demonstrate anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects, phenolic acids display antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, and alkaloids exhibit antimicrobial and antiviral properties. The presence of these bioactive compounds in Megastachya tenax has been attributed to its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and skin disorders. The pharmacological activities of these constituents have been validated through in vitro and in vivo experiments, providing scientific evidence for the medicinal properties of Megastachya tenax.",
