    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Megastachya tenax are maka tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. Maka tea is prepared by infusing the leaves of M tenax in hot water to treat various health conditions such as fever and rheumatism. Infusion is similar to tea but made with a larger amount of plant material and steeping time, often used for digestive issues. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the plant material in a solvent, used for its antimicrobial properties, while salve is a topical application of the plant's extract in a carrier oil, used for skin issues. Decoction is a method of extraction used for harder plant parts, such as roots, by boiling them in water to make a medicinal tea.",
